{{Quote|My uncle Nico, he was a true Jedi Master. All of us combined barely equal his power, wisdom, and will.|Tae Diath|<ref name="SWR 56" />}}
'''Nico Diath''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] who lived during the final [[Republic Classic era|decades]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. Diath was [[Diath family|descended]] from the ancient [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] Master [[Sidrona Diath]], and took his nephew [[Tae Diath|Tae]] as his [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]], helping him to control his [[Telepathy/Legends|telepathy]]. As a Jedi, Diath roamed the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] and emancipated more than one thousand [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]]. He rarely visited the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], but was regarded as a legend of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]. [[22 BBY/Legends|Four months]] after the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|initiation]] of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], Diath was assigned as the leader of a team, comprised of fellow Jedi Masters [[Jon Antilles]], [[Knol Ven'nari]], [[Fay]], and [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], on a [[Mission to Queyta|mission]] to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Queyta]].

Diath and the team were assigned to infiltrate a mobile [[Separatist Queyta base|Separatist facility]] that rode on one of Queyta's [[Magma/Legends|lava]] streams, and acquire the [[Antidote/Legends|antidote]] for [[swamp gas]], a chemical weapon the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatists]] planned to use against the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]]. After Diath's group infiltrated the base, they confronted Separatist agents [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]] and [[Durge/Legends|Durge]]. Durge shot two [[Skakoan/Legends|Skakoan]] sentries, which caused them to explode, and the ceiling of the facility to begin collapsing. Some lava fell on Diath as he stood on a catwalk, and he fell to his [[Death/Legends|death]] in the lava stream. Kenobi recovered the antidote and returned to the Jedi Temple as the only survivor of the mission. A [[Hologram/Legends|holographic]] memorial was held at the Jedi Temple in honor of Diath and the other fallen Masters.

==Biography==
{{Quote|<nowiki></nowiki>''Nico Diath'', part of the Diath clan that has produced a great number of Jedi Masters. He roamed the Outer Rim freeing more than one thousand slaves. The Hutts hated him&hellip;|Obi-Wan Kenobi, regarding Diath|<ref name="SWR 53" />}}
[[File:Diath_holo.jpg|thumb|left|100px|Diath was considered to be a legend in the Jedi Order.]]
Nico Diath, a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]], was born into a [[Diath family|family]] that was known for producing a number of [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]].<ref name="SWR 53" /> He was descended from the ancient [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] Masters [[Sidrona Diath|Sidrona]] and [[Dace Diath]], who both fought in the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]].<ref name="Tales of the Jedi Companion">''[[Tales of the Jedi Companion]]''</ref><ref name="Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War 1">[[Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War 1|''Tales of the Jedi – The Sith War'' 1]]</ref> During the final [[Republic Classic era|decades]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], he was [[Jedi training/Legends|trained]] in the ways of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] and eventually achieved the rank of Jedi Master.<ref name="SWR 53" /> During his time in the Order, Diath took his nephew [[Tae Diath|Tae]] as his [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]]. Whenever Tae lost control of his [[Telepathy/Legends|telepathy]], Diath made his nephew listen to his thoughts, which calmed the young man.<ref name="SWR 56" /> Diath rarely visited the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] on the [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] [[Capital/Legends|capital]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]; instead, he roamed the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] and liberated over one thousand [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]], which caused their [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] slave owners to hate him. By the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|beginning]] of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], during which the Galactic Republic waged war with the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]], Diath was regarded as one of the legends of the Jedi Order.<ref name="SWR 53" />

[[22 BBY/Legends|Four months]] into the Clone Wars, Diath [[Mission to Queyta|traveled]] to the [[Planet/Legends|world]] of [[Queyta]] and met with Jedi Masters [[Jon Antilles]], [[Fay]], and [[Knol Ven'nari]] in order to recover a sample of the [[Antidote/Legends|antidote]] for the Separatists' chemical weapon known as [[swamp gas]].<ref name="SWR 53" /> The Separatists had successfully tested the airborne gas against the [[Gungan/Legends|Gungan]] colony on [[Ohma-D'un/Legends|Ohma-D'un]], a [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of the planet [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]].<ref name="Republic 51">[[Republic 51|''Republic'' 51]]</ref> Diath was placed in charge of the team, and his group was soon joined by [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]]. After he arrived, Diath and his fellow Jedi successfully infiltrated the mobile [[Separatist Queyta base|Separatist facility]], which was located on a small island moving through one of the planet's [[Magma/Legends|lava]] streams.<ref name="SWR 53" />

After accessing the facility, Diath and Ven'nari noted the lack of [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droids]] guarding the base. As Ven'nari prepared to attack the guards that were manning the base, Antilles noted that the guards were [[Skakoan/Legends|Skakoans]]&mdash;a [[Species/Legends|species]] that breathed [[Methane/Legends|methane]] and was forced to wear pressurized [[Armor/Legends|armor]]&mdash;and that attacking them with a [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] would cause them to explode. Diath realized that the team would have to avoid the Skakoan sentries. Kenobi searched the facility's schematics and located the [[Laboratory/Legends|laboratory]] where the antidote was located. After reaching the laboratory, Diath and the Jedi confronted the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]] and the [[Gen'Dai/Legends|Gen'Dai]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Durge/Legends|Durge]], who were allied with the Confederacy. They informed Diath and his group that their [[Spy/Legends|spies]] had already informed them of the Jedi's presence in the facility. As Durge shot two of the Skakoans and caused them to explode, Ven'nari used her [[Pyrokinesis|pyrokinetic]] abilities with the Force to pull the fire toward her. After the fire subsided, Diath and the team found Ven'nari with extensive burns. He used the Force to comfort Ven'nari as she [[Death/Legends|passed away]].<ref name="SWR 53" />

[[File:NicoDiathDeath-Republic53.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Diath falls into a lava stream during the mission to Queyta.]]
When the facility started to sink into the lava stream due to the explosion caused by Durge, the four surviving Jedi pursued Ventress, who had the antidote in her possession. However, both the Dark Jedi and the bounty hunter caused the facility's ceiling to begin to collapse. Some lava fell on Diath as he stood on a catwalk, burning the Jedi Master and causing him to fall into the lava stream. Before Diath was incinerated, he implored Antilles, Fay, and Kenobi to get out of the facility.<ref name="SWR 53" />

===Legacy===
After Diath's death, Antilles and Fay were murdered by Durge and Ventress, respectively. Although only Kenobi survived, he was able to acquire the antidote and returned to the Jedi Temple on Coruscant. When Kenobi recuperated from his wounds, a [[Hologram/Legends|holographic]] memorial service was held in honor of Diath and the other three Jedi Masters.<ref name="SWR 53" /> During a [[Battle of Jabiim|Republic campaign]] on the planet [[Jabiim/Legends|Jabiim]], Tae Diath came to believe that his uncle was stronger and more powerful than he and his [[Padawan Pack|fellow Padawans]] combined. Yet, due to Diath's death, Tae was losing control of his telepathy.<ref name="SWR 56" /> Tae was killed during the conflict on Jabiim.<ref name="Republic 57">[[Republic 57|''Republic'' 57]]</ref>

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|Our ''only'' concern is retrieving a sample of the antidote, ''regardless'' of the risk. If we fail, the clone army is doomed.|Diath, regarding his Jedi team's mission to Queyta|<ref name="SWR 53" />}}
The Human male Nico Diath wore a set of [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Jedi apparel/Legends|Jedi robes]] and owned a lightsaber containing a blue [[Lightsaber crystal/Legends|crystal]]. He was regarded as one of the Jedi Order's nomads, rarely visiting the Jedi Temple on Coruscant. Diath, however, still fought for peace and freedom in the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]]. During the mission to Queyta, Diath made it a point to stress the importance of their mission, despite the risk involved. As Knol Ven'nari died, he took the time to ease her suffering. After her demise, he was determined to pursue the Dark Jedi Asajj Ventress. Before his death, he ordered Jon Antilles, Fay, and Obi-Wan Kenobi to flee from the facility.<ref name="SWR 53" />

==Powers and abilities==
{{Quote|When Nico was alive, he made me listen to his thoughts whenever I lost control. It was like listening to an ocean breathe.|Tae Diath, regarding his uncle Nico Diath|<ref name="SWR 56" />}}
Diath inherited the [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitivity]] of his family's bloodline, and eventually earned the rank of Jedi Master.<ref name="SWR 53" /> When he trained his nephew Tae&mdash;who was a telepath&mdash;Diath encouraged Tae to listen to his thoughts whenever his nephew lost control of his telepathy.<ref name="SWR 56" /> During the mission to Queyta, Diath demonstrated his ability with [[Telekinesis/Legends#Force flight|Force flight]], using this to infiltrate the Separatist facility.<ref name="SWR 53" />

==Behind the scenes==
Nico Diath was created by [[W. Haden Blackman]] for the standalone [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] [[Republic 53|''Blast Radius'']], the fifty-third issue of the ''[[Star Wars: Republic]]'' comic series. He was drawn in the issue by [[Brian Ching]]. Diath&mdash;along with Jon Antilles, Fay, and Knol Ven'nari&mdash;was indirectly mentioned in ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''{{'s}} entry on the mission to Queyta. He was also mentioned in ''[[The Official Star Wars Fact File 111]]'',<ref name="FF 111" /> and later received an entry in ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''.<ref name="CSWE: Diath, Nico">{{CSWECite|I|188-189|Diath, Nico}}</ref>

